[size=3][b]How to generate a map with cave system ?[/b][/size]

[quote][list=1]
[*][size=2]Go to to the random world generator (main menu / editing tools / random gen previewer)[/size]
[*]Configure your world
[*]Configure your cave options (bottom left of the rwg panel)
[*][size=2]Generate the configured world[/size]
[*][size=2]Create a new game in the generated world[/size]
[/list][/quote]
[b][size=3]
I didn't find any cave entrance, are you kidding me ?
[/size][/b]
[quote]Cave entrances are spread all over the map, they can be present as wilderness holes or may be hidden in regular prefabs. Some of them can be hard to find, so keep your eyes open ![/quote]
[size=3][b]
How to create cave prefabs ?[/b][/size]

[quote]A dedicated guideline is available [url=https://sites.google.com/view/caveprefabguideline/cave-prefab-guideline]here[/url], docuenting the specifications to create a valid cave prefab, and how to use the prefab editor plugin.[/quote]
[b][size=3]I Accidentally deleted TFP_HARMONY, how to get it back ?[/size][/b]

[quote][list]
[*]In steam, go to your games library and search for 7 days to die.
[*]Look for properties / local files / check local files integrity.
[*]Once the checking process is over, the folder TFP_HARMONY should be back in your mods folder
[/list][/quote]